.TH PRT-edit 8 "prt-#VERSION# Manual"
.SH NAME
prt-edit \- Edit the file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prt edit
.IR PKG
.RI [ FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit the \fIFILE\fR using the editor specified in the $EDITOR environment
variable. If \fIFILE\fR is not specified, \'Pkgfile\' is used.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
If the port has a \fIFILE\fR, then \fBprt\fR will try to open it using
a \fBEDITOR\fR. If \fBPAGER\fR is unset, then \fBprt(8)\fR will fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B prt-ls(8), prt-cat(8)
